This project applies Logistic Regression to a marketing dataset to predict whether a specific internet user will click on an advertisement based on their demographics and online behavior.
By analyzing features such as Daily Time Spent on Site, Age, Area Income, and Daily Internet Usage, the model identifies key patterns that lead to user engagement. 
The final model was trained using Scikit-Learn and achieved an impressive accuracy of 97%, providing a high-precision tool for optimizing digital advertising spend and targeting.
